<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Males of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. xishan" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xishan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. xishan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. albimana" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer embolus, larger cymbium flange and thicker, bar-shaped retrolateral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5A-D</figureCitation>
; see fig. 12B-D in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. assamensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. erlangping" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlangping">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. erlangping</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fimbriata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. labiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. orientalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quei" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. quei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. taiwanica" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zhaoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhaoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. zhaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the tegular furrow extending a membranous apophysis ventrally, the tegular apophysis obscure, and the embolus basally with a spinule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5A-C</figureCitation>
; see figs 10D, 7C, and 10A in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 6 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="37 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Murphy, J, Murphy, F, 1983. More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 6: 37 - 45" title="More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="6" year="1983">Murphy and Murphy 1983</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 661 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peng, XJ" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B11" refString="Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Xiao, XQ, Yin, CM, 1993. Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" title="Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae)." year="1993">Peng et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, and fig. 4B in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" author="Zhang, JX" journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="221 - 229" refId="B16" refString="Zhang, JX, Li, D, 2005. Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub)tropical China. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 53: 221 - 229, DOI: http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" title="Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub) tropical China." url="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" volume="53" year="2005">Zhang and Li (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, respectively); in addition, from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. assamensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fimbriata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the embolus being shortest (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5A-C</figureCitation>
; see figs 10D and 7C in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. erlangping" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlangping">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. erlangping</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the embolus being longer (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5A</figureCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. labiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter cymbium flange and thicker bar-shaped retrolateral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Female genital anatomy of Portia fajing sp. nov. A, B DL- 001 - 016 - 2013 (holotype) A epigyne, ventral view B vulva dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606781" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">4D</figureCitation>
; see fig. 10B in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. orientalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quei" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. quei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. taiwanica" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. taiwanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zhaoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhaoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. zhaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer embolus and bar-shaped retrolateral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5A-D</figureCitation>
; see fig. 6 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, J" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="37 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Murphy, J, Murphy, F, 1983. More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 6: 37 - 45" title="More about Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." volume="6" year="1983">Murphy and Murphy 1983</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 661 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peng, XJ" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B11" refString="Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Xiao, XQ, Yin, CM, 1993. Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" title="Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae)." year="1993">Peng et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, and fig. 4B in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" author="Zhang, JX" journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="221 - 229" refId="B16" refString="Zhang, JX, Li, D, 2005. Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub)tropical China. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 53: 221 - 229, DOI: http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" title="Four new and one newly recorded species of the jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Lyssomaninae &amp; Spartaeinae) from (sub) tropical China." url="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4619118" volume="53" year="2005">Zhang and Li (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, respectively). Females of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. xishan" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xishan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. xishan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differ from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. bawang" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bawang">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. bawang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by having a slightly wider epigynal orifice (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5E</figureCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fajing" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fajing">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fajing</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the larger epigyne orifice and distinctly sclerotised anterior orifice margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia xishan sp. nov. A-D LQ- 18 - 06 (holotype) A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F LQ- 18 - 06 B E epigyne, ventral view F vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606782" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">5E</figureCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. labiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
